  Stable for x86, wrt bug #506928

*sane-backends-1.0.24-r4 (21 May 2014)

  21 May 2014; Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org> +sane-backends-1.0.24-r4.ebuild:
  Enable multilib support, bug #493168.

  17 May 2014; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> sane-backends-1.0.24-r3.ebuild:
  Stable for alpha, wrt bug #506928

  14 May 2014; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> sane-backends-1.0.24-r3.ebuild:
  Stable for sparc, wrt bug #506928

  13 May 2014; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> sane-backends-1.0.24-r3.ebuild:
  Stable for ia64, wrt bug #506928

  12 May 2014; Chema Alonso <nimiux@gentoo.org> sane-backends-1.0.24-r3.ebuild:
  Stable for amd64 wrt bug #506928

  07 May 2014; Markus Meier <maekke@gentoo.org> sane-backends-1.0.24-r3.ebuild:
  arm stable, bug #506928

  14 Apr 2014; Jeroen Roovers <jer@gentoo.org> sane-backends-1.0.24-r3.ebuild:
  Stable for HPPA (bug #506928).

  06 Apr 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> sane-backends-1.0.24-r3.ebuild:
  Needs to be rebuilt with systemd subslot bumps

  25 Mar 2014; Mike Frysinger <vapier@gentoo.org>
  sane-backends-1.0.24-r3.ebuild:
  Disable backends by default if they require parallel ports.

  03 Mar 2014; Christopher Brannon <teiresias@gentoo.org>
  files/sane-backends-1.0.24-systemd_pkgconfig.patch:
  Fix build failures caused by an incorrect patch.

  03 Mar 2014; Christopher Brannon <teiresias@gentoo.org>
  sane-backends-1.0.24-r1.ebuild:
  Force stable sane-backends to depend on systemd-208 or less.

*sane-backends-1.0.24-r3 (03 Mar 2014)

  03 Mar 2014; Christopher Brannon <teiresias@gentoo.org>
  -sane-backends-1.0.24-r2.ebuild, +sane-backends-1.0.24-r3.ebuild,
  +files/sane-backends-1.0.24-systemd_pkgconfig.patch:
  Use pkg-config when linking against systemd (bug #502422).

  22 Feb 2014; Markus Meier <maekke@gentoo.org> sane-backends-1.0.24-r1.ebuild:
  arm stable, bug #497460

