*sane-backends-1.0.24-r1 (22 Oct 2013)

  22 Oct 2013; Christopher Brannon <teiresias@gentoo.org>
  -sane-backends-1.0.24.ebuild, +sane-backends-1.0.24-r1.ebuild,
  +files/sane-backends-1.0.24-unused-cups.patch:
  Remove *unused* automagic dependency, fix "make check" failure.
  sane-backends no longer depends on cups, but the detection code was
  still in the configure script. Also, fix make check failure due to
  incorrect hard-coded data. Closes bug #488658.

*sane-backends-1.0.24 (16 Oct 2013)

  16 Oct 2013; Christopher Brannon <teiresias@gentoo.org>
  +sane-backends-1.0.24.ebuild,
  +files/sane-backends-1.0.24-automagic_systemd.patch,
  +files/sane-backends-1.0.24-saned_pidfile_location.patch:
  Version bump.

*sane-backends-1.0.23-r2 (27 Aug 2013)

  27 Aug 2013; Christopher Brannon <teiresias@gentoo.org>
  +sane-backends-1.0.23-r2.ebuild,
  +files/sane-backends-1.0.23-automagic-cups.patch,
  +files/sane-backends-1.0.23-automagic-v4l.patch:
  Switch to virtual/libusb:1. Also remove automagic dependencies.

  Some of us were experiencing crashes with libusb 0.x, and they disappear
  with this change. See bug #480184. I also eliminated automagic
  dependencies on cups and v4l. See bug #479772.

  26 Aug 2013; Christopher Brannon <teiresias@gentoo.org> metadata.xml:
  Adopt package.

  21 Jul 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> -files/1.0.20-unbreak-udev.diff,
  -files/broken_coolscan.patch, -files/epson2fixes-1.0.19.patch,
  -files/fujitsu_DBG_LEVEL.patch, -files/genesys_io.patch,
  -files/sane-backends-1.0.22-freebsd.patch,
  -files/sane-backends-1.0.22-libv4l-0.8.3.patch,
  -files/sane-backends-1.0.22-xerox_mfp-usb.patch, -files/udev-rule-4.patch,
  -files/udev-rule-5.patch, -files/udev-rule-6.patch, -files/xerox-grey.patch,
  -sane-backends-1.0.17.ebuild, -sane-backends-1.0.18-r6.ebuild,
  -sane-backends-1.0.19-r2.ebuild, -sane-backends-1.0.20-r3.ebuild,
  -sane-backends-1.0.21-r1.ebuild, -sane-backends-1.0.22-r1.ebuild,
  -sane-backends-1.0.22-r2.ebuild, metadata.xml:
  Cleanup due #473480

  08 May 2013; Mike Frysinger <vapier@gentoo.org>
  sane-backends-1.0.23-r1.ebuild, sane-backends-1.0.23.ebuild:
  Make cross-compiling work.

  08 May 2013; Mike Frysinger <vapier@gentoo.org>
  sane-backends-1.0.23-r1.ebuild:
  Use standard `unpack` to unpack the combined tarball.

*sane-backends-1.0.23-r1 (15 Mar 2013)

  15 Mar 2013; Patrick Kursawe <phosphan@gentoo.org>
  +sane-backends-1.0.23-r1.ebuild,
  +files/sane-backends-1.0.23-saned_pidfile_location.patch,
  +files/kodakaio-fixes.patch, +files/saned.confd, +files/saned.initd:
  Bug #456018: Showing message about the "scanner" group.
  Bug #458472: Added files for openrc
  Bug #458580: No more linking to libsnmp unless specified.
  Bug #460252: Reacting on some QA issues.
  Bug #460440: Using debug output for debug message.


  22 Feb 2013; Patrick Kursawe <phosphan@gentoo.org>
  sane-backends-1.0.23.ebuild:
  Update to EAPI 5 for libgphoto2 stabilization, see bug #455500.

  06 Feb 2013; Patrick Kursawe <phosphan@gentoo.org>
  sane-backends-1.0.23.ebuild:
  Fixing the last fix.

  01 Feb 2013; Patrick Kursawe <phosphan@gentoo.org> sane-backends-1.0.23.ebuild:
  Bug #451822: If "threads" is not in USE, default-disable backends that
  require them.

